Yippee-kay-yay. We were only there for pre-dinner drinks and 2 bruschetta's but we instantly fell in love with the open atmosphere and hipster waitstaff (all of whom were very helpful, knowledgeable, and gainfully tattooed). Quirky wine list and tasty snacks were separated into clever and aptly named categories such as "Zippy" wines and "friendly" beers. Booom
